- Process line by line. Lines split at '\n'. Strip one trailing '\r' from each line. Columns are 1-based byte positions in the stripped line.
- Blank lines (all blanks or empty) skipped. Comment lines: first non-blank char is ';' or '#'.
- "[name]" — section header: trimmed name non-empty; blanks allowed around the header (i.e. leading blanks before '[', trailing blanks after ']'), nothing else on the line.
- key = value lines split at first '='. Trim key and value. Key must be non-empty, value may be empty.
