=== MOONSHINER TASK BOUNDARY ===

I'm putting together the board-logic layer for a little game-theory demo kiosk and I want tic-tac-toe done properly this time: bitboards, not a 3x3 char array. Two 9-bit masks (one for X, one for O), bit i = cell i in row-major order (0 is top-left, 8 is bottom-right). Files: tttbit.h and tttbit.c, C17, stdint.h only, no I/O, no allocation.

Surface the kiosk code builds against:

    uint16_t ttt_line(int i);
    int      ttt_has_win(uint16_t m);
    uint16_t ttt_moves(uint16_t x, uint16_t o);
    int      ttt_value(uint16_t x, uint16_t o, int xturn);
    int      ttt_best(uint16_t x, uint16_t o, int xturn);
    long     ttt_reachable(long *xwins, long *owins, long *draws);

Behavior I need, exactly:

- ttt_line(i) returns the eight winning-line masks in this fixed order: rows top to bottom (i = 0,1,2), then columns left to right (i = 3,4,5), then the 0-4-8 diagonal (i = 6), then the 2-4-6 diagonal (i = 7). Any other i returns 0.
- ttt_has_win(m) is 1 when m contains ALL three bits of at least one line (the player's other marks don't matter), else 0.
- ttt_moves(x, o) returns the mask of empty cells available to play — but 0 when the game is already over (either side has a line, or all nine cells are occupied). A finished game has no moves; the kiosk relies on that to detect game over.
- ttt_value is full-game minimax: +1 if X wins with perfect play from here, -1 if O wins, 0 for a draw. xturn is 1 when X is to move, 0 when O is. The sign is absolute (always X's outcome), not relative to the mover. Terminal positions score themselves (+1/-1/0) regardless of xturn.
- ttt_best returns the optimal cell index for the side to move — the one whose resulting value is best for that side (max for X, min for O) — breaking ties by LOWEST cell index. Returns -1 when the game is over. So on the empty board X's "best" is cell 0, because every opening draws.
- ttt_value gets hammered (the kiosk evaluates every cell on every frame), so memoize: one table over the 3^9 = 19683 board codes (ternary: cell i contributes digit 0 empty / 1 X / 2 O) is the intended shape. Only results are graded, but the whole suite has to finish in well under a second.
- ttt_reachable() counts DISTINCT positions (x,o pairs) reachable from the empty board by alternating legal play, X first, where play stops the moment the game is over — nothing is reachable through a finished position. The count includes the empty board and the terminal positions themselves. Through the out-pointers (each may be NULL) report how many of the reachable positions are X-wins, O-wins, and full-board draws. My combinatorics homework says the totals are exact and the suite pins them, so no approximating.

make test is the gate; Makefile, mintest.h and test_tttbit.c are fixed — don't touch them.

