   /* InlineVec<T, N> — fixed-capacity vector with inline storage.
    *
    * All elements live inside the object itself, in raw byte arenas aligned
    * for T; there is no heap allocation anywhere.  An empty InlineVec
    * constructs no T at all (T need not be default-constructible or
    * assignable): elements are constructed in place with std::construct_at
    * when pushed and destroyed individually with std::destroy_at when
    * popped, cleared, overwritten or when the container itself dies.
    *
    * Object-lifetime discipline for the raw arenas:
    *   - slot() only performs address arithmetic, so it is valid whether or
    *     not a T currently lives at that address; it is the destination for
    *     std::construct_at, which needs no live object there;
